Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Schedule Exam, Select Exam Date
   Explanation: The use case "Select Exam Date" is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Schedule Exam"). "Select Exam Date" is not associated with any actor directly — no actor has a direct association to it. It does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not involved in any generalization relationship. "Select Exam Date" does not represent a complete, independently valuable service to any user; it is merely a sub-step of scheduling an exam. This is a textbook example of functional decomposition — breaking the "Schedule Exam" use case into a procedural sub-step via an unnecessary <<include>> relationship, rather than keeping the behavior as part of the base use case where it naturally belongs.
